children.value: Quman has been sad lately :( No one knows about Quantum World, where he is from.
You can make him happy by passing the test he prepared.
Quman has quantum questions for you to test your knowledge.
You must solve these questions correctly.
First, he will ask you to build some quantum circuits.
To build the circuit: Drag and drop the gate you want into the correct place in Circuit Land.
Then, he will ask you quantum questions with multiple choices.
For all the questions, the closer you are to the correct answer, the happier Quman will be :)

events.comment:
Create one background instance for of each state.
Only the instance for the current state is shown.
Place the label over the backgrounds.
Show the right background accordingly to the new state.

Children instances must be resized when the button size change:
- backgrounds for each state are resized to take the full dimensions of the button
- the label is put back at the center of the button

The scale is set back to 1 because it means that the parent instance has the same dimensions as the union of its children instances.

eventsFunctionsExtensions.name: CancellableDraggable
eventsFunctionsExtensions.shortDescription: Allow to cancel the drag of an object (having the Draggable behavior) and return it smoothly to its previous position.
description: Add this behavior on an object with the Draggable behavior and the Tween behavior.
Use then the action to cancel the drag, and the behavior will smoothly animate the object back to its original position, using a tween animation.

eventsBasedBehaviors.description: Allow to cancel the drag of an object and make it smoothly return to its original position (with a tween).
eventsBasedBehaviors.name: CancellableDraggable

events.comment: Save the object position to be able to revert the dragging.
Enable back the Draggable behavior when the object comes back to its position before it was dragged.
